
### 2. **man_1_simple_shell**

.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "January 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple Unix shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIarguments\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell program is a basic command-line interface (CLI) that executes commands in an interactive shell. It reads user input, interprets it, and runs commands accordingly.

.SH OPTIONS
None. The shell runs interactively, reading input from the user and executing commands.

.SH COMMANDS
The simple_shell supports the following commands:

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.TP
.B cd
Changes the current directory.

.TP
.B help
Displays help information about built-in commands.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 if the command was executed successfully, otherwise returns 1.

.SH AUTHOR
Developed by Ichraq Najjar, Holberton School.

